# Portal Web Rules

## Scalability & Maintainability

### Component Architecture
- Follow atomic design: atoms (Button, Badge) → molecules (PatientCard) → organisms (PatientList) → pages
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks (`src/hooks/`)
- Keep components under 150 lines — split into smaller sub-components
- Co-locate component, types, and tests in the same directory when possible
- Use composition pattern: pass children/render props instead of massive prop drilling

### State Management
- Server state: React Server Components + fetch (default)
- Client state: `useState` for local, `useContext` for shared within a page
- Form state: controlled components with validation
- Do NOT introduce a global state library (Redux, Zustand) unless justified with ADR
- Cache server data with React Query when real API is connected

### Performance
- Use React Server Components by default — add `'use client'` only when needed
- Lazy-load heavy components with `dynamic()` import
- Optimize images with `next/image`
- Minimize client-side JavaScript — prefer server-side data fetching
- Use `React.memo` only when profiling shows re-render issues (don't premature optimize)

## i18n

- All user-visible strings must use i18n translations
- Import `useLocale` hook for client components
- Translation files in `packages/i18n/locales/{vi,en}/<namespace>.json`
- Key pattern: `namespace.context.element`
- Never hardcode Vietnamese or English strings in components

## Components

- Use shadcn/ui components from `@/components/ui/`
- Shared layout components in `@/components/layout/`
- Feature components in `@/components/<feature>/`
- Use Lucide React for icons
- Note: shadcn/ui v4 (base-nova) does NOT have `asChild` prop — use native HTML elements for links

## Data Fetching

- Use Server Components for initial data fetch where possible
- Client components for interactive features (forms, filters, real-time updates)
- API calls go through `@/lib/api.ts` — centralized API client with error handling
- Never call backend services directly from components — always go through API layer
- Handle loading, error, and empty states for every data-fetching component

## Error Handling

- Show user-friendly error messages using i18n keys
- Display toast notifications for async operations (save, delete, submit)
- Implement error boundaries for critical sections
- Log client-side errors for debugging

## Viewer Integration

- OHIF viewer URL configured via `NEXT_PUBLIC_OHIF_URL` env var
- Deep-link format: `{OHIF_URL}/ohif/viewer?StudyInstanceUIDs=...&taskId=...&caseId=...`
- Always open viewer in new tab (`target="_blank"`)
- Use `@/lib/viewer.ts` for constructing viewer URLs

## Accessibility

- All interactive elements must be keyboard navigable
- Use semantic HTML elements (`<nav>`, `<main>`, `<article>`, `<button>`)
- Add `aria-label` to icon-only buttons
- Color contrast must meet WCAG 2.1 AA
